hopobject.body: Do you know each other? artificial intelligence in medicine pdf COAM is rated two notches below the China sovereign (A /Stable), reflecting ownership by the central government, and strong operational and strategic ties with the government, resulting in a strong likelihood of extraordinary government support if needed. COAM's rating also takes into account dilution of the policy role and expected reduction in shareholding by the government. COAM is therefore classified as a dependent public sector entity under Fitch's criteria.
